{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1769468782,"nonce":"A8PeENY4xbF952I6L3IG7oEUEGM=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87l9S4w","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/46","origin":"github"},"title":"Workspace Integration: Add Copilot CLI-Specific Onboarding \u0026 Support","message":"# Workspace Integration Analysis: Copilot CLI Support Gap\n\n## Executive Summary\n\nThis ROS2 agent workspace has sophisticated agent infrastructure (Antigravity, multi-agent workflows) but is **not optimally configured for GitHub Copilot CLI**. The workspace provides excellent documentation and tooling for specialized agent platforms but lacks:\n\n1. **Copilot CLI-specific onboarding** - No dedicated quick-start for CLI users\n2. **Status reporting that matches CLI capabilities** - Limited integration with CLI-native commands\n3. **Slash command discoverability** - Workflows are documented but not accessible via CLI patterns\n4. **CLI-friendly environment setup** - Identity configuration requires manual steps instead of CLI integration\n5. **Clear CLI vs. Agent role distinction** - Mixed documentation for multiple agent types without clear separation\n\n## Current State Assessment\n\n### ✅ Strengths\n- **Excellent foundational infrastructure**:\n  - `.agent/WORKFORCE_PROTOCOL.md` - Clear multi-agent coordination\n  - `.agent/AI_IDENTITY_STRATEGY.md` - Git identity management\n  - `.agent/ROADMAP.md` - Central task tracking\n  - Comprehensive workflow catalog (17 workflows in `.agent/workflows/`)\n  - Knowledge base for ROS2 patterns and best practices\n\n- **Well-structured documentation**:\n  - `README.md` - Clear usage patterns\n  - `AGENT_ONBOARDING.md` - Detailed checklist\n  - `AGENT_INDEX.md` - Workflow discovery\n  - Role-based permissions (Framework Engineer, ROS Developer, Ops Agent)\n\n- **Automated operations**:\n  - Pre-configured scripts (setup, build, clean, status)\n  - Makefile with common targets\n  - Pre-commit hooks available\n\n### ⚠️ Gaps for Copilot CLI\n\n#### 1. **No Copilot CLI-Specific Onboarding** (HIGH PRIORITY)\n- `AGENT_ONBOARDING.md` uses identity format `Copilot CLI Agent` but doesn't explain *why* or *when* a CLI user would use this vs. Antigravity\n- No quick-reference for \"I'm using Copilot CLI — where do I start?\"\n- Missing: CLI-specific environment checks (is Copilot CLI available? version?)\n\n**Recommendation**: Create `.agent/COPILOT_CLI_QUICK_START.md` with:\n- Detection: \"How to know you're running Copilot CLI\"\n- Quick 3-step setup (vs. 6+ for general agents)\n- CLI-native commands and syntax\n- Link to CLI documentation\n\n#### 2. **Status Report Doesn't Leverage CLI Capabilities** (MEDIUM PRIORITY)\n- Current `status_report.sh` relies on `vcs`, `git`, and shell commands\n- Copilot CLI has native tools for workspace analysis, GitHub status, etc.\n- Status output is plain text; CLI could surface structured data\n\n**Recommendation**: Extend `/check-status` workflow to:\n- Detect if running under Copilot CLI\n- Use CLI APIs for faster GitHub checks (PRs, issues, branch status)\n- Format output for CLI UI consumption\n- Cache results to avoid rate limiting\n\n#### 3. **Slash Commands Are \"Meta\" — Not CLI-Native** (MEDIUM PRIORITY)\n- `.agent/workflows/` defines tasks but not as CLI slash commands\n- CLI users expect `/build`, `/test`, etc. to be discoverable in the terminal\n- Current pattern: users must ask the agent verbally or read `.agent/AGENT_INDEX.md`\n\n**Recommendation**: Create `.agent/CLI_COMMANDS.md` mapping:\n- Slash commands → agent workflows\n- CLI-native command equivalents (e.g., `colcon build` → `/build`)\n- When to use each approach\n\n#### 4. **Git Identity Configuration Is Manual** (LOW PRIORITY)\n- Requires running `.agent/scripts/configure_git_identity.sh` manually\n- No CLI hook to auto-configure on first session\n- Identity string is hardcoded in `AGENT_ONBOARDING.md` but not auto-detected\n\n**Recommendation**: Add CLI integration point:\n- Script to auto-detect agent platform (read `USER` env var or CLI version info)\n- Option to auto-run configuration during first workspace check\n\n#### 5. **Mixed Agent Roles in Documentation** (LOW PRIORITY)\n- `PERMISSIONS.md` defines 3 roles (Framework Engineer, ROS Developer, Ops Agent)\n- `AGENT_ONBOARDING.md` mentions these roles but doesn't map Copilot CLI to a specific role\n- CLI users might not know whether they're acting as a \"ROS Developer\" or \"Framework Engineer\"\n\n**Recommendation**: Clarify in new `.agent/COPILOT_CLI_QUICK_START.md`:\n- Copilot CLI typically acts as \"ROS Developer\" role\n- When to switch roles (if needed)\n- Permission scopes for CLI operations\n\n#### 6. **Environment Sourcing Is Implicit** (LOW PRIORITY)\n- `AGENT_ONBOARDING.md` mentions `source .agent/scripts/env.sh`\n- CLI might not have this sourced automatically\n- Some workflow scripts assume ROS environment is set up\n\n**Recommendation**: \n- Verify `env.sh` is sourced at start of all critical workflows\n- Add check in `/check-local-status` to warn if ROS env is not loaded\n\n---\n\n## Proposed Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Documentation (Week 1)\nCreate new files for CLI-specific guidance:\n\n1. **`.agent/COPILOT_CLI_QUICK_START.md`** (300 lines)\n   - What is Copilot CLI?\n   - 3-step setup specific to CLI\n   - Common CLI workflows\n   - Link to GitHub Copilot CLI docs\n\n2. **`.agent/CLI_COMMANDS.md`** (150 lines)\n   - Mapping of slash commands to workflows\n   - CLI-native equivalents\n   - Examples for each command\n\n3. **Update `.agent/AGENT_ONBOARDING.md`** (50 lines)\n   - Add \"Copilot CLI Users: Start Here\" section\n   - Link to new COPILOT_CLI_QUICK_START.md\n   - Keep general steps but note CLI-specific shortcuts\n\n### Phase 2: Workflow Enhancement (Week 2)\nUpdate existing workflows to support CLI detection:\n\n1. **Enhance `/check-status` workflow**\n   - Detect Copilot CLI environment\n   - Use CLI APIs when available\n   - Fallback to shell commands for compatibility\n\n2. **Create `.agent/scripts/detect_cli_env.sh`**\n   - Identify if running under Copilot CLI\n   - Export CLI capabilities to workflows\n   - Version info and feature detection\n\n### Phase 3: Integration Points (Optional, Week 3+)\nIf deepening CLI support:\n\n1. **Create CLI-specific GitHub MCP server integration**\n   - Pre-populate CLI with common ROS2 commands\n   - Enable faster PR/issue searches\n\n2. **Add Copilot CLI-specific error messages**\n   - When workflows fail, suggest CLI-specific debugging steps\n   - Example: \"Use `copilot task --debug` to see logs\"\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n✅ **Copilot CLI users can:**\n- Understand their setup in \u003c 5 minutes (vs. 15+ currently)\n- Run `/check-status` and see relevant output immediately\n- Discover available workflows via CLI patterns\n- Know which role they're acting as\n\n✅ **Documentation is:**\n- Findable: linked from main README\n- Actionable: no vague statements\n- Tested: verified with fresh clone + CLI setup\n\n✅ **Backward compatibility:**\n- Antigravity users unaffected\n- Existing workflows still work\n- Shell-based operations still available\n\n---\n\n## Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|-----------|--------|-----------|\n| CLI docs become stale | Low | Medium | Link to upstream CLI docs; mark doc version |\n| Mixed role confusion persists | Medium | Low | Clear role assignment in quick start |\n| Status checks slow down CLI | Low | Medium | Cache results; add async mode |\n| New docs not maintained | Medium | Medium | Add owner in CONTRIBUTING.md |\n\n---\n\n## Notes\n\n- This analysis assumes Copilot CLI is similar to other CLI agents (bash-based, terminal-driven)\n- Specific CLI features (e.g., task subcommands, API integration) should be verified against official Copilot CLI documentation\n- User feedback will refine recommendations; consider A/B testing documentation approaches","files":null}]}